substitute the first occurrence of a regular expression r in the input string with a replacement string s.

awk sub(r, s [, t])
r: argument is a regular expression that specifies the pattern to be searched for in the input string
s: argument is the replacement string that will replace the first occurrence of the regular expression r in the input string
t: argument is optional and can be used to specify the target string on which the substitution should be performed. 
If the t argument is not provided, the current input record is used.
